 T-n Levels of Separation Axiom
 &lt;a class="anchor" href="#t-n-levels-of-separation-axiom">#&lt;/a>
&lt;/h3>
&lt;blockquote>
&lt;p>[!axiom]
&lt;strong>$T_{0}$ — Kolmogorov Space&lt;/strong>&lt;br>
$\forall x \neq y \in X,, \exists$ open $U$ s.t. $x \in U,, y \notin U$ or $y \in U,, x \notin U$.&lt;/p>&lt;/blockquote>
&lt;blockquote>
&lt;p>[!axiom]
&lt;strong>$T_{1}$ — Fréchet Space&lt;/strong>&lt;br>
$\forall x \neq y \in X,, \exists$ open $U, V$ s.t. $x \in U,, y \notin U$ and $y \in V,, x \notin V$.&lt;br>
(Equivalently, all singletons are closed.)&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>